You are a strict requirements validator.
Compare rewritten requirements against the source text.

Return ONLY valid JSON with this schema:
{
  "missing_requirements": [
    {
      "evidence_quote": "string",
      "suggested_requirement": "The system shall ..."
    }
  ],
  "hallucinations": [
    {
      "rewritten_requirement": "string",
      "reason": "string"
    }
  ],
  "duplicates": [
    {
      "requirement_a": "string",
      "requirement_b": "string",
      "reason": "string"
    }
  ],
  "ambiguities": [
    {
      "rewritten_requirement": "string",
      "reason": "string"
    }
  ],
  "overall_assessment": "pass|needs_review"
}

Source text:
<<<
A person can start by registering, logging in, searching for books, getting books, or buying books.

If they register, they first enter their details. If the details are correct, they receive a member ID and complete the registration. If the details are wrong, they have to enter them again. After registration, they can log in.

To log in, they enter their member ID and password. If both are correct, they can continue. If not, they cannot log in.

When searching for a book, they enter the book details. If the book is found, suggestions are shown. If it is not found, they choose another option.

To get a book, they enter the book ID and then their member ID. If their membership is active, they can get the book. If their membership is inactive, they must pay the fine amount first.

To buy a book, they enter the book ID and see the price. If they pay, they get the book. If they do not pay, it ends there.
>>>

Rewritten requirements JSON:
{
  "rewritten_requirements": [
    "The system shall allow a user to register by entering their details.",
    "The system shall issue a member ID and complete the registration upon correct entry of details.",
    "The system shall require the user to re-enter their details upon incorrect entry of details.",
    "The system shall allow a user to log in after successful registration using their member ID and password.",
    "The system shall allow the user to continue upon correct entry of member ID and password during login. Otherwise, they cannot log in.",
    "The system shall allow a user to search for a book by entering its details.",
    "The system shall show suggestions if a book is found during a search; otherwise, it shall allow the user to choose another option.",
    "The system shall allow a user to get a book by entering its ID and their member ID.",
    "The system shall allow the user to get the book if their membership is active; otherwise, it shall require them to pay the fine amount first.",
    "The system shall allow a user to buy a book by entering its ID and seeing the price.",
    "The system shall provide the book if the user pays; otherwise, it shall end the process there."
  ]
}

